    "body": "The Trilinos package contains the comment:\n\n```\n    # not everyone has py-numpy activated, keep it disabled by default to avoid\n    # configure errors\n    variant('python',       default=False, description='Build python wrappers')\n```\n\nLater, it specifies a dependency on `python`, but not on `py-numpy`. If Trilinos actually depends on `numpy` when Python is used, then it needs to say so in its dependencies.\n",
